{'text': 'If a drug were legal and available, people would very likely choose to use it over illegal drugs, just because it would be fun to use. \xa0 Drug use is fun. \xa0 Drugs are freedom.'}
{'text': "Do you know of any countries that have legalized drugs? I haven't read much about the effects, but from what I've read, it seems like the results have been pretty negative."}
{'text': "What if we're trying to eradicate drugs completely, but we don't know exactly how to do it?"}
{'text': "I don't think that the government should be in the business of deciding what kind of drugs are legal and what kind of drugs aren't."}
{'text': "Why would I want to do drugs? Just because I want them doesn't mean I should be allowed to have them."}
{'text': "I don't think that legalizing drugs will lead to a decrease in the use of drugs. I think that's one of the main problems with this whole issue."}
{'text': "If someone wants to legalize drugs, why don't they legalize alcohol?"}
{'text': "Legalization is a slippery slope problem. If we legalize marijuana, then next year it's legal to do cocaine."}
{'text': "As I said earlier, I think legalizing drugs is a bad idea. I don't like the idea that the government could decide on what drugs are legal and what are not."}
{'text': "What if the fact that we're spending so much tax money on the war on drugs is why we have so much crime in this country in the first place?"}

{'text': 'Drugs are not that big of a concern for most people compared to other things in life. It is not a good idea to encourage people to use drugs just because it is a socially accepted behavior.'}
{'text': "It's always better to try before you buy. Also, I don't think that it's such a good idea to legalize a drug just to make it easier to buy."}
{'text': 'To me, there is a huge difference between illegal drug users and drug dealers. Illegal drug users get to choose whether or not they want to use drugs.'}
{'text': 'I think that it would be great if the government took a bigger role in drug policy reform. The government should be looking out for the human rights of its citizens.'}

{'text': 'If people want to use drugs, they should be able to do so without being punished for doing so. They should not have their lives ruined because of the fact that they still want to use drugs.'}
{'text': "People who want to use drugs shouldn't have to go to jail for it."}
{'text': 'The government has no right to decide what type of drugs people should be allowed to use, only the people themselves do. If people want to use drugs, then they should be allowed to do so.'}
{'text': "It's a good thing that our government isn't making these decisions. If it were, we wouldn't have to live in fear that our friends may make bad life decisions while high."}

{'text': "It's easy for me to say I don't want to vote for someone who supports marijuana legalization, because I don't want to vote for someone who supports the criminalization of something as harmless as marijuana..."}
{'text': "If we're going to legalize drugs, then we should legalize them for all purposes, and not just for medical purposes."}
{'text': "If we're going to legalize drugs, then we should legalize all drugs, not just marijuana. Why can't we legalize all kinds of drugs at the same time?"}
{'text': "When it comes to recreational drugs, we're not talking about getting high off a joint. We're talking about having fun, relaxing, and enjoying life."}
{'text': 'People should be able to use whatever substances they want as long as they are not hurting anyone else.'}
{'text': 'When the drug war first started, it was primarily an effort to reduce the amount of alcohol that was being consumed by young people.'}
{'text': "Legalizing drugs would be a step in the right direction, but it's not going to solve the problem of drug abuse."}

{'text': 'If we legalize drugs for recreational purposes, what will we do with all the illegal drugs that are still on the streets? Will they be legalized too? Will they all be legalized at the same time?'}
{'text': "It's much easier to regulate alcohol than it is to regulate drugs. This makes sense, because alcohol is so much more deadly than drugs."}

{'text': 'If the government decides to legalize drugs, it will most likely come down to one of two options: 1) The government will decide to require people to use their drugs or 2) The government will decide...'}
{'text': "At the very least, it's important for kids (and adults) to be educated about drugs, so that they know what they're getting into when they use them."}
{'text': "What if you're an addict and you can't stop using drugs? And what if you're already addicted, and you have no idea what will become of you if you continue down this path?"}

{'text': "I think that legalizing drugs for recreational purposes is one of the best things that can happen to the world. I don't think that the government should be in the business of punishing people for using drugs."}
{'text': "This is a policy debate, not a moral one. What's wrong with legalizing drugs if it reduces drug use rather than causes more crime? But that's a discussion for another day."}
{'text': "If you legalize drugs, you're going to get a whole lot more people addicted to drugs. \xa0To me, this is not a good thing."}
{'text': 'The point of legalizing drugs is to reduce the evils of drug abuse, addiction, and crime. The question is, how can we do that effectively?'}
